MetalSharp Wine 11.5 patch: D3DMetal loader compatibility minimal safe candidate

Generated from the restored safe loader-compat candidate after the 2026-07-05
GPTK4 investigation. Applies after the host ABI patch from the Wine source root
with patch -p0.

This patch intentionally avoids ntdll.spec exports and avoids Darwin
signal/syscall/TLS/GS changes. It implements the Phase-A loader compatibility
surface only:

- backend-gated D3DMetal payload search priority via MS_D3DMETAL_PAYLOAD_DIR
- backend-gated PE image registration through MS_D3DMETAL_SHARED_PATH
- backend-gated D3DMetal bridge image writability for the bridge DLL allowlist
- a narrow RtlVirtualUnwind2 null optional-output guard observed during GPTK4
  crash diagnostics

Known blocker retained outside this patch: GPTK4 dxgi/d3d12/d3d11 create calls
still crash at the native task_policy_set / Rosetta boundary on the new all-PE
Wine 11.5 runtime. Do not treat this patch as full D3DMetal runtime proof.

